</ul>
                          <p class="page-info-header__description">State lawmakers continue to introduce voting and elections bills at a furious pace.</p>
                                    <div class="page-info-header__meta">
                            <div class="page-info-header__dates">
                <div class="page-info-header__date"><strong>Last Updated: </strong>May 28, 2021</div>
                <div class="page-info-header__date"><strong>Published: </strong>February 24, 2021</div>
              </div><!--/.page-info__date-->

                        </div><!--/.page-info__meta-->
                      </div><!--/.page-info-header__after-title-->
                  </div><!--/.page-info-header__left-->
        <div class="page-info-header__right" data-swiftype-index="false">
                      <figure class="page-info-header__image">

              <picture>
                <source srcset="https://www.brennancenter.org/sites/default/files/styles/1400x800/public/2021-02/20210224_RS_GT1229444017RM_1630x932.jpg?itok=KT8xk5zv" media="(min-width: 1401px)">
                <source srcset="https://www.brennancenter.org/sites/default/files/styles/1400x800/public/2021-02/20210224_RS_GT1229444017RM_1630x932.jpg?itok=KT8xk5zv 2x, https://www.brennancenter.org/sites/default/files/styles/700x400/public/2021-02/20210224_RS_GT1229444017RM_1630x932.jpg?itok=EHhRGAo- 1x" media="(min-width: 700px)">
                <img srcset="https://www.brennancenter.org/sites/default/files/styles/700x400/public/2021-02/20210224_RS_GT1229444017RM_1630x932.jpg?itok=EHhRGAo- 2x, https://www.brennancenter.org/sites/default/files/styles/350x200/public/2021-02/20210224_RS_GT1229444017RM_1630x932.jpg?itok=E2jGP77_ 1x" alt="Voters waiting in line to vote. ">
              </picture>

              <figcaption class="page-info-header__credit">Sean Rayford/Getty</figcaption>
            </figure>
                    
                  </div><!--/.page-info-header__right-->
      </div><!--/.page-info-header__inside-grid-->
    </div><!--/.page-info-header__inside-->
  </div><!--/.page-info-header__inside-wrap-->
</header><!--/.page-info-header-->

  <div class="field-content__main">
          

<article class="page-body">
  <div class="page-body__inside container-small wysiwyg-styles ">
    <div id="position-11367" class="chapter">
                                                <p>In conjunction with the Brennan Center&rsquo;s&nbsp;<a href="https://www.brennancenter.org/our-work/research-reports/voting-laws-roundup-may-2021"><strong>report</strong></a>&nbsp;on state voting proposals, below is a list&nbsp;of the restrictive and expansive bills that we are tracking to date.&nbsp;<br><br>
As of May 14, 2021, legislators have introduced&nbsp;<strong>389 bills</strong>&nbsp;with&nbsp;<strong>restrictive provisions</strong>&nbsp;in&nbsp;<strong>48 states</strong>. Twenty-two bills with restrictive provisions have already been enacted. In addition, at least<strong>&nbsp;61&nbsp;bills with restrictive provisions in 18 states are moving&nbsp;</strong>through legislatures:&nbsp;<strong>31 have passed at least one chamber</strong>, while another 30 have had some sort of committee action (e.g., a hearing, an amendment, or a committee vote).<br><br>
Note that, in some cases, a single bill can have provisions with both restrictive and expansive effects.</p>

<p><iframe aria-label="table" frameborder="0" height="591" id="datawrapper-chart-U1eij" scrolling="no" src="https://datawrapper.dwcdn.net/U1eij/1/" style="width: 0; min-width: 100% !important; border: none;" title="Bills Restricting Voting Access&nbsp;"></iframe><script type="text/javascript">
//<![CDATA[
